    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly limited to static quasi-static compression-bending comparison and the regulatory submission does not claim dynamic or environmental equivalence. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. The credibility evidence package, including the methodological framework described in the peer-reviewed literature (see referencesIdentifier), supports an overall Accepted determination at Medium assurance level.",
